### Railway Backend API Examples
### Use with REST Client extension in VS Code or similar tools
### Replace {{baseUrl}} and {{token}} with your actual values

@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api
@token = your_jwt_token_here

### Health Check
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

###

### Register New User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "testuser",
  "email": "test@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User"
}

###

### Login User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "identifier": "test@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePass123"
}

###

### Get Current User Profile
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Update User Profile
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/update-profile
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Updated",
  "lastName": "Name",
  "username": "updateduser"
}

###

### Change Password
PUT {{baseUrl}}/auth/change-password
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "currentPassword": "SecurePass123",
  "newPassword": "NewSecurePass456"
}

###

### Get All Users (Admin Only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users?page=1&limit=10&search=test
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get User by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/USER_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Update User Status (Admin Only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/USER_ID_HERE/status?isActive=false
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Update User Role (Admin Only)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/users/USER_ID_HERE/role?role=admin
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Delete User (Admin Only)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/USER_ID_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Get User Statistics (Admin Only)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/stats/overview
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Upload Profile Picture
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/profile-picture
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="profilePicture"; filename="profile.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

 ./path/to/your/image.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary--

###

### Upload Multiple Files
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/files
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary

------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="document1.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf

< ./path/to/document1.pdf
------WebKitFormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="image1.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./path/to/image1.jpg
------WebKitFormBoundary--

###

### Get File Information
GET {{baseUrl}}/upload/info/FILENAME_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Delete Profile Picture
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/upload/profile-picture
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Delete Specific File
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/upload/file/FILENAME_HERE
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

###

### Error Examples

### Invalid Registration (Missing Fields)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "test",
  "email": "invalid-email"
}

###

### Invalid Login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "identifier": "nonexistent@example.com",
  "password": "wrongpassword"
}

###

### Unauthorized Request (No Token)
GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me

###

### Forbidden Request (User trying to access admin endpoint)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users

